MyDAL
======

An extend of DAL of OracleAdapter to support schema/database descriptor.
Yet this stage MyDAL only support schema descriptor in 
select_limitby and left outer of OracleAdapter.

Feel free to rename class MyDAL and mydal.py to something you preffer,
e.g filename my_preffer_name.py and class MyPrefferName(DAL): ...

How to use it:
1. Copy my_preffer_name.py into your applications/your_app/modules
2. In your database modules, e.g db.py do:
    
		from my_preffer_name import MyPrefferName, MyTable
		
		# change db = DAL(...) to
		db = MyPrefferName('oracle://...')

		...
    db.define_table('comment',
        Field('name'),
        Field('description','text'),
        migrate=False, # make sure to not create the table
        sequence_name='comment_seq', # default is comment_sequence
        trigger_name='comment_trg', # default is comment_trigger
        table_class=MyTable # notice i use customized Table, that support schema
		)
		# set migrate to True so that the table is will be created
		db.comment.set_schema('other_app.', migrate=True, _adapter=db._adapter) 

		# now you have a _tablename = 'other_app.comment'
		# _sequence_name = 'other_app.comment_seq'
		# _trigger_name = 'other_app.comment_trg'
		

